A 45-year-old man accused of raping two young girls in a Pretoria hotel has abandoned his bail application. Courtesy of #DStv403 PRETORIA - A 45-year-old man accused of raping two young girls in a Pretoria hotel has abandoned his bail application. The man is also being charged with kidnapping the two minors, aged 11 and 13. READ: Man charged with rape of two minors previously convicted An order was issued on Monday that the accused's identity is to not be made public. The man is reportedly a family friend of one of the victims and revealing his identity might mean her identity would also be exposed. Hotel staff confronted him after hearing the children screaming.